SIMPLE: equilibration
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Equilibration
<hw>E`qui*li*bra"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Act of keeping a balance, or state of being balanced;
equipoise.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In . . . running, leaping, and dancing, nature's laws of
<qex>equilibration</qex> are observed.</q> <rj><qau>J.
Denham.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The process by which animal and
vegetable organisms preserve a physiological balance.</def> <rj><au>H.
Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Equilibrious</ent>⟦br⟧
